        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 4:59PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
West Valley City, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Salt Lake City, West Valley City, Bountiful, West Jordan,
Taylorsville, North Salt Lake, Centerville, Woods Cross, West
Bountiful, Kearns, Salt Lake City International Airport, Magna,
Oquirrh, and Antelope Island State Park.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 308 and 321.
Interstate 80 in Utah between mile markers 105 and 119.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
